<subSubSection pageId="155" pageNumber="156" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="155.[151,1436,1287,1927]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1720,1744]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This porcelain crab seems to replace 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Randall" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[777,910,1720,1744]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinctipes">
<emphasis box="[777,791,1721,1744]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[811,910,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">cinctipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
south of Point Conception, 
<collectingRegion box="[1254,1371,1720,1744]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">California</collectingRegion>
. It is extremely common. As many as 22 individuals were found under a single rock with area of about 0.9 m 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1344,1352,1756,1770]" fontSize="6" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">2</superScript>
among rocky rubble near Point Fermin, Los 
<collectingRegion box="[571,663,1794,1818]" country="Philippines" name="Angeles" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Angeles</collectingRegion>
County, 
<collectingRegion box="[766,883,1794,1818]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">California</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sloan, L. &amp; Anderson, S. &amp; Pernet, B." box="[894,1106,1794,1819]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" pagination="159 - 166" refId="ref236452" refString="Sloan, L., Anderson, S. &amp; Pernet, B. (2010) Kilometer-scale temporal variation in prevalence of the rhizocephalan Lernaeodiscus porcellanae on the porcelain crab Petrolisthes cabrilloi. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 30, 159 - 166." type="journal article" year="2010">
Sloan 
<emphasis box="[966,1016,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
reported that it is parasitized by the rhizocephalan 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F.Muller" authorityYear="1862" box="[403,710,1831,1855]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Lernaeodiscidae" genus="Lernaeodiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Kentrogonida" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porcellanae">
<emphasis box="[403,710,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Lernaeodiscus porcellanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They also noted that the sizes of the largest individuals in a population varied geographically even among sites separated by only a few kilometers, perhaps in response to food.
</paragraph>
